__link wp-block-kadence-singlebtn\"><span class=\"kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-ic_exit kt-btn-icon-side-left\"><svg viewBox=\"0 0 8 8\"  fill=\"currentColor\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\"  aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M1 0l-1 1 1.5 1.5-1.5 1.5h4v-4l-1.5 1.5-1.5-1.5zm3 4v4l1.5-1.5 1.5 1.5 1-1-1.5-1.5 1.5-1.5h-4z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"kt-btn-inner-text\">Show Less<\/span><\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1) Play with Them \/ Playtime with Toys<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats are curious animals that love to play. Playing with your cat is not only a fun activity but also essential for their physical and mental health. In this section, we'll discuss the importance of playtime for cats and provide examples of how to keep your feline friend engaged and entertained.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Provides Exercise<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Playing is a natural way for cats to exercise, and it helps to keep them healthy and fit. Regular playtime can also help prevent obesity, which can lead to health issues. Running, jumping, and chasing toys are all great exercises for cats.<br>Example: You can play with your cat using a laser pointer, and they will chase the light around the room, providing a fun and exciting workout.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Strengthens the Bond Between You and Your Cat<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Playing with your cat can help strengthen the bond between you two. It helps them associate you with fun and positive experiences, leading to a closer relationship.<br>Example: You can spend time with your cat by playing with them using interactive toys like feather wands. It's a great way to build trust and establish a deeper bond.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Provides Mental Stimulation<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats are intelligent creatures that require mental stimulation. Playtime can provide an opportunity for them to engage in natural hunting and stalking behaviors, keeping their minds sharp.<br>Example: You can use puzzle feeders, which hide treats or kibble in various compartments that cats need to work to open. It's a great way to provide mental stimulation while also satisfying their natural hunting instincts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create a Play Area<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can make playtime even more fun by creating a play area in your home. Cat trees, scratching posts, and tunnels are excellent options to keep your cat engaged and entertained.<br>Example: You can create a cat tree by stacking up boxes or getting a pre-made one. It's a perfect spot for your cat to play, rest, and watch the world go by.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Playing with your cat is an essential part of cat ownership, providing exercise, mental stimulation, and strengthening the bond between you two. Try to provide a variety of toys and create a play area in your home to keep your cat happy, healthy, and entertained.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_57d5cf-ed .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_57d5cf-ed .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_57d5cf-ed\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2) Cuddle Time \/ Cuddle with Them<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats are social creatures that crave attention and affection, and cuddling is a great way to give them the love they desire. Here are some reasons why cuddling with your cat is essential:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bonding<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cuddling with your cat is a wonderful way to create a strong bond between you two. Spending quality time with your cat can deepen your relationship and make your cat feel loved and secure.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Comfort<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats love to snuggle up to their owners, and it can provide them with a sense of comfort and security. Cuddling can be especially comforting for cats that may have anxiety or are recovering from an illness.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Stress relief<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cuddling with your cat can be a stress-relieving activity for both you and your pet. The act of petting and holding a cat can help reduce cortisol levels, the hormone associated with stress.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Relaxation<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cuddling with your cat can also promote relaxation and calmness. The rhythmic sound of your cat's purring can have a soothing effect on your body and mind.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>After a long day at work, you can unwind by snuggling with your cat on the couch. This can help you relax and forget about any stress from the day. You can also provide your cat with the affection and attention they crave, making them feel happy and loved. Whether you're watching a movie or reading a book, cuddling with your cat can be a comforting and enjoyable activity for both of you.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_c48220-80 .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_c48220-80 .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_c48220-80\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3) Outdoor Adventures \/ Take Them for a Walk<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Many cats love to explore the great outdoors and experience new sights, sounds, and smells. While some cats are strictly indoor pets, others can safely venture outside with proper precautions. Here are some ways to provide your cat with an outdoor adventure:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Take your cat for a walk on a leash<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like dogs, some cats can be trained to walk on a leash. This is a great way to safely expose your cat to the outdoors and give them some exercise. It's important to use a harness that fits properly and to choose a safe location away from traffic and other hazards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Provide a safe outdoor enclosure<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a yard or outdoor space, you can create a safe enclosure where your cat can play and explore. This can be done with a variety of materials, including fencing, mesh, and netting. It's important to make sure the enclosure is secure and free from any potential hazards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Let your cat explore on their own<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a cat who loves to roam, you can provide them with a safe outdoor environment where they can explore on their own. This can be done with a cat-proofed balcony, catio, or other enclosed space. It's important to make sure your cat has access to food, water, and shelter and is protected from any potential dangers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can take your cat to a nearby park or nature trail and walk them on a leash, allowing them to experience the outdoors in a safe and controlled environment. Alternatively, you can create a catio or outdoor enclosure in your backyard where your cat can play and relax while being protected from predators and other hazards.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_44c658-4c .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_44c658-4c .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_44c658-4c\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4) Grooming Sessions<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Grooming is an essential part of a cat's daily routine, and as a cat parent, you can help keep your furry friend's coat clean and healthy. By grooming your cat, you can create a special bond with them and show them that you care. Brushing your cat's fur helps to distribute natural oils throughout their coat, keeping their fur soft and shiny.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Grooming your cat also allows you to check for any potential health issues, such as skin irritations, fleas, or ticks. Regular grooming can help prevent these issues from becoming more severe. Additionally, grooming can help to reduce the amount of hair that your cat sheds, which can be particularly helpful if you have allergies.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When grooming your cat, it's important to use the right tools, such as a soft brush or comb, and to work gently to avoid hurting your cat. Start by stroking your cat's back with the brush, gradually working your way to other areas, such as their belly and legs. Use treats or catnip to help make the grooming experience more enjoyable for your cat.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Set aside a specific time each day or week to groom your cat. Create a relaxing environment, such as playing soft music or burning a calming candle, to help your cat feel more comfortable. Use a soft brush or comb and work gently, stopping if your cat becomes agitated or uncomfortable. You can also offer treats or catnip to make the experience more enjoyable for your cat.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_dad9f3-23 .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_dad9f3-23 .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_dad9f3-23\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5) Movie Night \/ Watch TV Together<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Spending a cozy night in with your cat can be a fun and relaxing way to bond with them. Here are some tips for having a movie night with your furry feline friend:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choose the right movie<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When selecting a movie or show to watch, consider your cat's interests. Cats enjoy watching shows and movies with birds, mice, and other animals. You can also try a nature documentary or a slow-paced movie with plenty of cuddling opportunities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create a comfortable space<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Set up a cozy space for you and your cat to relax in. This can include a comfy blanket, pillows, and a spot for your cat to curl up next to you. Make sure there are no distractions or loud noises that might frighten your cat.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Treats and snacks<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats love treats, so make sure to have some on hand for your movie night. You can offer them their favorite treats or even whip up some homemade cat treats.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Interact with your cat<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>While you're watching the movie, interact with your cat by petting them, talking to them, and offering them treats. This will help strengthen your bond and make your cat feel loved.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You and your cat can cuddle up on the couch with a warm blanket and some popcorn to watch a nature documentary about birds. As you watch the birds on the screen, your cat's eyes will widen, and they may even chirp or paw at the screen. You can stroke your cat's fur while they sit in your lap, making them feel secure and loved. Don't forget to offer your cat some of their favorite treats to munch on during the movie.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_8047c0-46 .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_8047c0-46 .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_8047c0-46\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">6) Teach Them Tricks<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While many people believe that cats are untrainable, this couldn't be further from the truth. With patience and consistency, you can teach your cat a variety of tricks and commands that will not only entertain you but also strengthen your bond with your feline friend.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some tips for training your cat to do tricks:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Start with basic commands<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Begin with simple commands such as &#8220;sit&#8221; and &#8220;come&#8221; before moving on to more complex tricks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use positive reinforcement<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats respond well to positive reinforcement, such as treats and praise. Reward your cat with a small treat and lots of verbal praise whenever they successfully perform a trick.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Keep training sessions short<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats have short attention spans, so it's important to keep training sessions short and focused. Five to ten-minute sessions a few times a day are ideal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Be patient<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Training your cat can take time and patience, so don't get discouraged if they don't learn a trick right away. Keep practicing, and eventually, they will catch on.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can start with teaching your cat to sit. Hold a treat above their head and slowly move it back towards their tail. As their head moves up, their rear end will naturally lower to the ground. As soon as they sit, give them a treat and lots of praise. With repetition, your cat will quickly learn to sit on command. You can then move on to more complex tricks such as high five or spin.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_661f89-a8 .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_661f89-a8 .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_661f89-a8\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">7) Massage Them<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Massaging your cat is an excellent way to show them some love and affection. Here are some benefits of massaging your cat:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Reduces stress and anxiety<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Massaging your cat can help to reduce stress and anxiety, as it promotes relaxation and calms the nervous system.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Improves blood circulation<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Massaging your cat helps to improve blood circulation, which can boost their immune system and keep them healthy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Relieves muscle tension<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Just like humans, cats can experience muscle tension, which can cause discomfort and pain. Massaging your cat can help to relieve muscle tension and promote comfort.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To massage your cat, follow these simple steps:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Find a comfortable and quiet spot<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Choose a quiet and peaceful location to massage your cat. This will help to reduce distractions and create a relaxing environment.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Get your cat comfortable<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you start massaging your cat, make sure they are relaxed and comfortable. Pet them gently and speak in a soothing voice to help them feel at ease.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Start with gentle strokes<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Begin massaging your cat with gentle strokes on their head and neck. Use your fingers to apply light pressure and work your way down to their shoulders and back.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Use circular motions<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Use circular motions with your fingers to massage your cat's muscles. Apply gentle pressure, and pay attention to any areas where your cat seems to be experiencing discomfort.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Massage for 5-10 minutes<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Massage your cat for 5-10 minutes at a time, and be sure to take breaks if your cat becomes restless or agitated.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can massage your cat while they are sitting on your lap or lying down. Start by gently stroking their head and neck, then work your way down their back with circular motions. Pay attention to their body language and any areas where they seem to be experiencing tension or discomfort. Finish the massage with some gentle strokes and praise your cat for being so good!<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_f8be4e-7b .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_f8be4e-7b .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_f8be4e-7b\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">8) Share a Meal Together<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cats love to be near their humans and may show interest in what their humans are eating. Sharing a meal with your cat can be a unique way to bond with them and can also provide them with mental stimulation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When sharing a meal with your cat, it's essential to be mindful of what foods are safe for them to eat. Some human foods can be toxic to cats, so it's best to stick with cat-friendly treats or food that's specifically made for cats.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also make a mealtime routine with your cat, where you both eat together at the same time. This can provide structure and routine for your cat, which they often enjoy.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Example:<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you're having a meal, you can share a small portion of unsalted cooked chicken or fish with your cat. You can also give them a treat made specifically for cats or offer them a small amount of wet food.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While you eat, you can place your cat's food or treat in a separate bowl near you so that they can eat with you. You can also talk to your cat, offer them a little food, and stroke them gently while they eat.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_e9a532-64 .kt-block-spacer{height:60px;}.wp-block-kadence-spacer.kt-block-spacer-_e9a532-64 .kt-divider{border-top-width:1px;height:1px;border-top-color:var(--global-palette1, #3182CE);width:54%;border-top-style:solid;}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-spacer aligncenter kt-block-spacer-_e9a532-64\"><div class=\"kt-block-spacer kt-block-spacer-halign-center\"><hr class=\"kt-divider\"\/><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">9) Bonus Advice<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>But before I'd like to offer some personal advice and precautions to keep in mind before spending time with your adorable feline friend. Here are some essential steps to take:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Get to Know Your Cat: Why Researching Your Feline Friend is Key Before Spending Time with Them<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It's crucial to learn everything you can about cats before spending time with them. This includes their specific breed, likes, dislikes, behavior, and personalities. Make sure to determine whether your cat has a breed-specific weakness that may affect their social interactions with you. For example, Persian cats are prone to health diseases, so it's best to consult with a veterinarian before engaging in vigorous play with them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tailoring Your Bonding Time: How to Develop a Bonding Routine That Works for Your Unique Cat<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Every cat is unique, so what works for one may not work for another. Observe your cat's behavior, personality, and comfort level to determine the best way to bond with them. You can develop a bonding routine tailored to their preferences, such as gently caressing their chin or enticing them with treats. If your cat is shy and awkward, you may pet them with your eyes until they're ready to bond with you.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Preparing to be a Cat Parent: Tips for Choosing the Right Breed and Ensuring a Healthy Relationship with Your Feline Friend<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you're considering bringing a kitten home, it's important to discover yourself as a cat parent. Be mindful of the breed of cats you wish to adore, as this can greatly affect the nature and quality of your relationship with them. Check whether you're allergic to particular cat breeds before adopting one. If you are, a Siberian or Russian Blue, which produce fewer Fel d1 protein allergens, may be ideal for you.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, spending time with your adorable cat can be a joyous experience, but it's important to take the necessary precautions to ensure a safe and enjoyable time for both you and your feline friend. By researching cats, observing your cat's behavior, and discovering yourself as a cat parent, you can build a strong and lasting bond with your furry companion.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Spending time with your cat can be incredibly rewarding and beneficial for both you and your pet. From playing with toys to cuddling up on the couch, there are many adorable ways to bond with your furry feline friend. So, next time you're looking for something to do, why not spend some quality time with your cat? They'll love you even more for it.<\/p>\n\n\n<style>.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col,.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col:before{border-top-left-radius:0px;border-top-right-radius:0px;border-bottom-right-radius:0px;border-bottom-left-radius:0px;}.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col{column-gap:var(--global-kb-gap-sm, 1rem);}.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col{flex-direction:column;}.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col > .aligncenter{width:100%;}.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col:before{opacity:0.3;}.kadence-column_af659f-e7{text-align:center;}.kadence-column_af659f-e7{position:relative;}@media all and (max-width: 1024px){.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col{flex-direction:column;}}@media all and (max-width: 767px){.kadence-column_af659f-e7 > .kt-inside-inner-col{flex-direction:column;}}<\/style>\n<div class=\"wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column_af659f-e7 kb-section-dir-vertical inner-column-1\"><div class=\"kt-inside-inner-col\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\" style=\"text-transform:uppercase\"><strong>Save It For Later<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-wp-embed is-provider-pinterest wp-block-embed-pinterest\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" title=\"9 Effective Ways To Spend Time With Your Cat\" src=\"https:\/\/assets.pinterest.com\/ext\/embed.html?id=1089519334831879928&#038;src=oembed#?secret=ON6b4fsoeg\" data-secret=\"ON6b4fsoeg\" height=\"775\" width=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>As a seasoned animal expert, I&#8217;ve got many ways to spend time with my cat for countless 